Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) Requirements:

Total Loan Applications:

Calculate the total number of loan applications received within a specified period.
Monitor Month-to-Date (MTD) loan applications.
Track Month-over-Month (MoM) changes in loan applications.
Total Funded Amount:

Assess the total amount of funds disbursed as loans.
Keep an eye on the MTD total funded amount.
Analyze MoM changes in the total funded amount.
Total Amount Received:

Track the total amount received from borrowers to evaluate cash flow and loan repayments.
Monitor the MTD total amount received.
Observe MoM changes in this metric.
Average Interest Rate:

Calculate the average interest rate across all loans.
Track the average interest rate MTD.
Monitor MoM variations in interest rates to gain insights into the lending portfolio's cost.
Average Debt-to-Income Ratio (DTI):

Evaluate the average DTI for all borrowers to assess their financial health.
Compute the average DTI MTD.
Track MoM fluctuations in the average DTI.


